I thought I would share this script, its been circulating a bit but I feel it is a nice one to have in your toolkit.
Have you ever had to remove a LUN from a cluster and thought &ldquo;Do I really need to detach all the LUN&rsquo;s, before un-mapping from my SAN?&rdquo;
 Unmount Datastore Detach LUN Un-map from SAN Rescan Cluster  Well here is a handy script with output.

As I was upgrading my VDP-A environment from 5.5 to 5.8 the upgrade failed due to the following error.
&ldquo;Please make sure you have at least 20GB for repo, 10GB for var, and 1GB for root partition.&rdquo;
Upon further research there seems to be an issue from 5.5.1 and 5.5.5 appliances with the /space partition filling up due to PostGres events. The issue can be resolving by installing the following VDP patch (vdp_patch-5.
